                <note rend="inline" type="source">393.1123 Seymour, Walter F./16: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Minister in China</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">MacMurray</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Peking</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1928-08-04T10:00:00+08:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">August 4, 1928—10 a.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                        <lb/>[Received 12 noon.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>598. My 545, July 17, 7 p.m. Following telegram has been sent to Nationalist
                    Minister for Foreign Affairs [and] is reported for your information.</p>
                <quote rend="blockquote">
                    <p>“Again referring to my despatch of May 10 [<hi rend="italic">15</hi>?]<note
                            n="51" xml:id="d245fn51">See telegram No. 377, May 21, from the Minister
                            in China, <ref target="#pg_286">p. 286</ref>.</note> concerning the
                        murder of Dr. Seymour, and to that of your predecessor of May 19th<note
                            n="52" xml:id="d245fn52">See despatch of May 28 from the Chinese
                            Commissioner of Foreign Affairs at Shanghai to the American consul
                            general, <ref target="#pg_287">p. 287</ref>.</note> stating that an
                        investigation had been ordered, I have the honor once more to request
                        information as to what has been done towards the apprehension and punishing
                        of those responsible for this crime.”</p>
                </quote>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">MacMurray</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
